 DEEP MAGIC n. An awesomely arcane technique central to a program or system,
esp. one not generally published and available to hackers at large (compare
BLACK ART). one which could only have been uttered by a true WIZARD. Compiler
optimization techniques and many aspects of OS design used to be DEEP MAGIC;
many techniques in cryptography, signal processing, graphics and AI still
are. Compare HEAVY WIZARDRY. Esp. found in comments of the form "Deep magic
begins here...".